## Security Fix Plan

### Background

7 open Dependabot alerts across 3 packages — all transitive, all patched:

| Alerts | Package | Severity | CVE | Fix |
|--------|---------|----------|-----|-----|
| #111-114 | minimatch (4 versions: 3.x, 8.x, 9.x, 10.x) | High | CVE-2026-26996 (ReDoS) | pnpm override |
| #110 | ajv < 6.14.0 | Medium | CVE-2025-69873 (ReDoS) | pnpm override |
| #108-109 | devalue <= 5.6.2 (docs/) | Low | GHSA-33hq / GHSA-8qm3 | pnpm override in docs/ |

### Task 1: Remove @sentry/typescript (source of tslint → minimatch 3.1.2)

@sentry/typescript was only used for its tsconfig.json (strict TS settings).
It dragged in tslint (deprecated since 2019) → minimatch 3.x (vulnerable).

Actions:
- Inlined all relevant compilerOptions from @sentry/typescript/tsconfig.json
  directly into tsconfig.build.json and removed the 'extends' line.
- Removed @sentry/typescript from devDependencies.

### Task 2: Remove rimraf and @types/rimraf

rimraf 2.7.1 was a direct dep with one call site (src/utils/files.ts).
@types/rimraf pulled in @types/glob -> glob@13 -> minimatch@10.1.1 (vulnerable).

Actions:
- Replaced rimraf(dir, cb) with fs.rm(dir, { recursive: true }, cb) using
  Node 22 built-in (same callback signature, no await needed).
- Updated 'clean' script from 'rimraf dist coverage' to 'rm -rf dist coverage'.
- Removed rimraf and @types/rimraf from devDependencies.

### Task 3: Add pnpm.overrides for minimatch (alerts #111-114)

After removing @sentry/typescript/@types/rimraf, all remaining minimatch
consumers are on the 10.x line. A blanket override is safe:

  "minimatch": ">=10.2.1"

Note: version-range keyed overrides (e.g. "minimatch@>=10.0.0 <10.2.1")
do not reliably work in pnpm 10 for already-compatible resolutions — pnpm
resolves the version once and doesn't re-evaluate against the override
selector. A blanket override is the reliable workaround when all consumers
are on the same major version line.

### Task 4: Add pnpm.overrides for ajv (alert #110)

ajv 6.12.6 is pulled in by eslint → @eslint/eslintrc. The fix is:

  "ajv@<6.14.0": "^6.14.0"

Important: must use ^6.14.0, NOT >=6.14.0. The >= form would resolve to
ajv v8 which has an incompatible API (crashes eslint with 'Cannot set
properties of undefined (setting defaultMeta)').

### Task 5: Fix devalue in docs/ (alerts #108-109)

devalue <= 5.6.2 is a transitive dep via the Astro/Starlight stack.
Added to docs/package.json pnpm.overrides:

  "devalue": ">=5.6.3"

